A4.text: Chopin was born in Żelazowa Wola and grew up in Warsaw, which in 1815 became part of Congress Poland.

A5.text: Frédéric François Chopin was born in Żelazowa Wola, 46 kilometres (29 miles) west of Warsaw, in what was then the Duchy of Warsaw, a Polish state established by Napoleon.
